# EduAI Backend Environment Configuration
# NOTE: This project now uses a unified .env file located at the project root (../.env)
# Copy the .env.example from the project root and place it as .env in the project root directory

# For reference, the backend requires these variables:
# APP_NAME, VERSION, DEBUG, HOST, PORT
# SECRET_KEY, ALGORITHM, ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES, REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_DAYS
# SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY
# GEMINI_API_KEY, GEMINI_MODEL, GEMINI_API_URL
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS, DATABASE_URL
# RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS, RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW

# The unified .env file at the project root contains both VITE_ prefixed variables 
# for the frontend and regular variables for the backend.

# To set up:
# 1. Copy c:\projects\EduAI\.env.example to c:\projects\EduAI\.env
# 2. Fill in your actual values
# 3. The backend will automatically read from ../env (project root)